recentFeedback.text:
From <@W5QE8QS90> (not in this channel):
&gt; Historically Uploads/Downloads have only been available by CC Desktop and Adobe Home built by their custom workers and as you are highlighting they do not support content from Projects.
&gt; 
&gt; ACPC kicked off <https://jira.corp.adobe.com/browse/ACPC-12131|ACPC-12131>  initiative a few months back to centralize support for this across all UAB/P experiences. As you can see in this epic <https://jira.corp.adobe.com/browse/CCPROJ-13180|CCPROJ-13180>, the work for download is pretty much done, we are just waiting for Indesign and Illustrator conversion workers to address some error handling cases before we release the feature to production. We expect this to be completed around end of the month.
&gt; 
&gt; As for DVA, specifically Squirrel, you should expect downloads to be enabled consistently across Adobe Home and Firefly Home around end of month/early April. We also have now these new workers in place that anyone can use, so Squirrel may also implement download of assets within the media panel - assuming you are not worried about Illustrator and InDesign conversion.
